== Overview == Simple hot springs are relatively common across the {{ill|Japanese archipelago|ja|日本列島|12=draft}} . They are defined by containing less than 1 gram of dissolved substances per kilogram of water while being at least 25&nbsp;°C at the source. In simpler terms, these springs leave relatively few residues upon evaporation. This has led to misunderstandings, with some perceiving simple hot springs as "mere water" or of lower quality. However, the classification focuses solely on the amount of solute, not its composition. Consequently, simple hot springs encompass a wide variety of water qualities.
