[[File:Kuronagi-onsen01.JPG|link=https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E3%83%95%E3%82%A1%E3%82%A4%E3%83%AB:Kuronagi-onsen01.JPG|right|thumb|'''単純温泉である黒薙温泉露天風呂''']] '''Simple Hot Springs''' (単純温泉, Tanjun Onsen) is a classification of {{ill|hot spring|ja|温泉|1=Onsen|1=Onsen|qq=draft|qq=draft}}water quality based on signage standards in Japan. It is categorized under {{ill|Therapeutic hot springs|ja|温泉#療養泉|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
== Definition of Water Quality == Among hot springs regulated by the {{ill|Hot Springs Law|ja|温泉法|1=Onsen Act|1=Onsen Act|1=Onsen Act|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , those with a temperature of 25&nbsp;°C or higher containing less than 1000 milligrams of dissolved substances per kilogram of water, excluding gases, are classified as simple hot springs{{sfn|山村|2015|p=7}} .
== Overview == Simple hot springs are relatively common across the {{ill|Japanese archipelago|ja|日本列島|qq=draft|qq=draft}} . They are defined by containing less than 1 gram of dissolved substances per kilogram of water while being at least 25&nbsp;°C at the source. In simpler terms, these springs leave relatively few residues upon evaporation. This has led to misunderstandings, with some perceiving simple hot springs as "mere water" or of lower quality. However, the classification focuses solely on the amount of solute, not its composition. Consequently, simple hot springs encompass a wide variety of water qualities.
Some simple hot springs exhibit characteristics of other types of springs based on their solute composition ratios. Others contain trace amounts of diverse substances. Notably, even {{ill|moor springs|ja|モール泉|1=Moor hot spring|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<nowiki/>can be categorized as simple hot springs. For instance, the {{ill|Tokachigawa Onsen|ja|十勝川温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in Hokkaido produces a colored simple hot spring from moor layers and is recognized as a {{ill|Hokkaido Heritage|ja|北海道遺産|qq=draft|qq=draft}} for its uniqueness{{sfn|山村|2015|p=53}}
.
== Comparison of Old and New Classifications == The correspondence between old and new classifications is as follows:
{| class="wikitable" |+ Comparison of Old and New Water Quality Names{{r|新旧泉質名対照表}}
! Old Classification ! New Classification ! Acidity (pH) |- | Simple Hot Spring || Simple Hot Spring || Less than 8.5 |- | Simple Hot Spring || Alkaline Simple Hot Spring || 8.5 or higher{{sfn|山村|2015|p=7}}
|}
== Benefits == Based on water quality, the following health benefits are associated with simple hot springs{{r|温泉療養のイロハ}} * {{ill|General Indications|ja|一般的適応症|1=General Indications for hot spring use|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* [[:en:Insomnia|Insomnia]]
